# v12-real-codex-pm-architect-smoke Architecture

## Architecture Summary

This architecture defines a docs-only smoke feature for validating the V12 automation pipeline handoff from a real Codex PM stage to a real Codex Architect stage.

The feature ID is `v12-real-codex-pm-architect-smoke`.

The intended behavior is limited to documentation generation, document-path consistency checks, stage-status evidence, and confirmation that no production code or trading-sensitive code path is changed.

The requirements source for this architecture is:

`docs/requirements/2026-06-16-v12-real-codex-pm-architect-smoke-requirements.md`

The target architecture document path is:

`docs/design/2026-06-16-v12-real-codex-pm-architect-smoke-architecture.md`

Automation metadata also references alternate no-hyphen date paths such as:

`docs/requirements/20260616-v12-real-codex-pm-architect-smoke-requirements.md`

`docs/design/20260616-v12-real-codex-pm-architect-smoke-architecture.md`

Downstream agents must treat the hyphenated date paths from the PM requirements and this architecture as the stage target paths, and must report the no-hyphen metadata paths as a documentation or pipeline consistency note. They must not silently normalize or ignore the mismatch.

This feature does not introduce product behavior. It does not modify API routes, Streamlit UI, market data providers, strategy logic, stock-pool filters, risk evaluation, execution policy, backtesting behavior, broker integration, or runtime configuration.

The architecture goal is to provide enough structure for downstream planning, development, testing, review, and acceptance stages to validate the PM-to-Architect smoke path while preserving docs-only scope.

